Sodium bicarbonate
Baking soda = E500
Na+HCO3-
white solid
production: Na2CO3 + CO2 + H2O -> 2 NaHCO3
thermal decomposition: 2 NaHCO3 -> Na2CO3 + H2O + CO2
antacid: NaHCO3 + HCl -> NaCl + H2O + CO
leavening agent: NaHCO3 + H+ -> Na+ + CO2 + H2O
odor remover, cleaning agent

Ammonia
NH3
colourless gas, pungent smell
production
- Haber process (high pressure and temperature): N2 + 3 H2 -> 2 NH3
fertilizer production, fuel, coolant
product of amino acid deamination, converted to urea

Sodium carbonate
Washing soda = E500
Na2CO3
white solid
production, Solvay process:
: NaCl + NH3 + CO2 + H2O -> NaHCO3 + NH4Cl
: 2NaHCO3 -> Na2CO3 + H2O + CO2
: 2NH4Cl + CaO -> 2NH3 + CaCl2 + H2O
cleansing agent, raising agent, glass manufacture

Calcium oxide
Quicklime
CaO
white solid
production: CaCO3 -> CaO + CO2 (temperature 900°C)
basic oxygen steelmaking, cement making, glass making

Sulfuric acid
H2SO4
colorless odorless liquid
highly corrosive
fertilizer production
exotermic hydration: H2SO4 + 2 H2O -> 2 H3O+ + SO4-
production, contact process:
: S + O2 -> SO2
: 2 SO2 + O2 -> 2 SO3 (catalyst V2O5)
: H2SO4 + SO3 -> H2S2O7
: H2S2O7 + H2O -> 2 H2SO4

Phosphoric acid
H3PO4
colorless solid
production, wet process: mineral treated with sulfuric acid
fertilizer production

Hydrofluoric acid
HF + H2O
colorless solution
highly corrosive
production: CaF2 + H2SO4 -> 2 HF + CaSO4
stored in PTFE containers

Nitric acid
HNO3
colorless liquid
highly corrosive
light decomposition: 4 HNO3 -> 2 H2O + 4 NO2 + O2
production: 3 NO2 + H2O -> 2 HNO3 + NO
fertilizer production

Formaldehyde
CH2O
colorless gas, pungent smell
production: 2 CH3OH + O2 -> 2 CH2O + 2 H2O
aqueous solution (formalin) used to store animal specimens

Vanadium oxide
V2O5
yellow solid
sulfuric acid production, ferrovanadium production

Sodium hydroxide
NaOH
white solid
production
- Chloralkali process: 2NaCl + 2H2O -> Cl2 + H2 + 2NaOH

Sodium chlorate
NaClO3
white solid
production: NaCl + 3 H2O -> NaClO3 + 3 H2
chlorine dioxide production

Sodium chlorite
NaClO2
white solid
chlorine dioxide production

Chlorine dioxide
ClO2
yellowish gas
production: NaClO2 + 1⁄2 Cl2 → ClO2 + NaCl
pulp bleaching (paper production)

Hydrogen peroxide
H2O2
pale blue liquid
production: Anthraquinone process
antiseptic, bleaching

Anthracene
C14H10
three fused benzene rings
precursor to dyes

Alizarin
C14H8O4
dihydroxyanthraquinone isomer
red dye

Chloroform
CHCl3
colorless liquid, strong smelling, dense
production:
: CH4 + Cl2 -> CH3Cl + HCl
: CH3Cl + Cl2 -> CH2Cl2 + HCl
: CH2Cl2 + Cl2 -> CHCl3 + HCl
precursor to PTFE, anesthetic

Benzene
C6H6

Polytetrafluoroethylene (PTFE)
(C2F4)n
wire insulation, non-stick coating

Sodium fluoride
NaF
white solid
water fluoridation, dental health
HF + NaOH -> NaF + H2O

Potassium permanganate
KMnO4
purple-black solid
disinfection

DDT (Dichlorodiphenyltrichloroethane)
C14H9Cl5
colorless odorless solid
insecticide, restricted, causes eggshell thinning

Hydrogen sulfide
H2S
colorless gas, foul odor, flammable
toxic, produced by microbial breakdown of organic matter in absence of oxygen

Vinyl chloride
H2C=CHCl
colorless gas, sweet odor, toxic, flammable
precursor to PVC
production: ClH2C=CH2Cl -> H2C=CHCl + HCl

Trichloroethylene
colorless liquid, sweet odor, toxic
Cl2C=CHCl
solvent

Tetrachloroethylene
colorless liquid, sweet odor
Cl2C=CCl2
solvent

Aldrin
colorless solid
insecticide, restricted
production: hexachlorocyclopentadiene + norbornadiene

Norbornadiene
production: cyclopentadiene + acetylene

Chlordane
white solid, toxic
insecticide, restricted
production: hexachlorocyclopentadiene + cyclopentadiene + chlorine

Dichlorodifluoromethane
R-12 / Freon-12
CCl2F2
colorless gass
refrigerant, banned, damages ozone layer

Phthalocyanine
four isoindole units linked in ring by nitrogens
applications: dyes and pigments
